My bet is that he wants back in the game because he wants to put things right and he wants to get up and make a contribution. When he was attorney general he was the sheriff of Wall Street. For those of you who saw the great documentary "Client 9: The Rise and Fall of Eliot Spitzer," you saw a man who was capable of great self reflection. When asked whether he had powerful Wall Street, insurance and banking forces, arrayed against him, he answered that he did but he also said that they couldn't have gotten him if he didn't do wrong.
